# Synthetic-data projects: raw/processed CSVs are reproducible by rerunning
# each project's python/generate_and_load_data.py. Where the project also uses SQL
# (customer_retention_behavior, supply_chain_inventory) the .db IS committed
# under <project>/sql/database/; where it uses Excel instead (sales_analytics_pipeline,
# industry_operations_cost) the .xlsx workbook under <project>/excel/ IS committed
sales_analytics_pipeline/python/data/raw/
sales_analytics_pipeline/python/data/processed/
customer_retention_behavior/python/data/raw/
customer_retention_behavior/python/data/processed/
industry_operations_cost/python/data/raw/
industry_operations_cost/python/data/processed/
supply_chain_inventory/python/data/raw/
supply_chain_inventory/python/data/processed/

# Wastewater project uses a real dataset (UCI) - raw CSV is the actual
# source data and IS committed; only the processed copy is regenerated
# by load_and_clean.py, so that one's ignored like the others
wastewater_effluent_quality/python/data/processed/

